Date: Thu 23 Feb 2017
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=22996


Infection with _Marteilia refringens_, Norway
---------------------------------------------
Information received on 23 Feb 2017 from Dre Kristina Landsverk, Chief Veterinary Officer, Norwegian Food Safety Authority, Ministry of Agriculture and Food, Brumunddal, Norway

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 22 Feb 2017
Date of confirmation of the event: 22 Feb 2017
Reason for notification: First occurrence of a listed disease in the country
Casual agent: _Marteilia refringens_
Nature of diagnosis: suspicion, necropsy
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1(2017-1): 11507 Agapollen, Bremnes, Bomlo, Hordaland
Date of start of the outbreak: 22 Feb 2017
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: pond
Water type: salt water
Population type: farmed
Production system: semi-closed
Affected animals:
Species / Morbidity / Mortality / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Blue mussel (_Mytilus edulis_) / 2 (scale 0 to 5) / 2 (scale 0 to 5) / - / - / - / - / -
Affected population: The mussels that were sampled are wild and found in the aquaculture farm with flat oysters, _Ostrea edulis_.

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Epidemiological comments: The Norwegian Food Safety Authority (NFSA) notifies a suspicion of _Marteilia sp._ on blue mussels in an aquaculture farm. For the 1st time this disease is suspected in Norway, a 1st occurrence in the country. During the routine surveillance, 30 blue mussels and 30 flat oysters were collected from the oyster pool (lagoon) on the Norwegian west coast. The oysters appeared healthy, but 12 of the mussels did not. The histopathological examination will be followed up with PCR as fast as possible. There is need for verification by European Union Reference Laboratory.

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals

Measures to be applied: traceability; modified stamping out; control of wildlife reservoirs

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Institute of Marine Research (National laboratory)/Blue mussel (_Mytilus edulis_) / histopathological examination / 22 Feb 2017 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

