Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[_Marteilia refringens_ is a protozoan parasite of the phylum Cercozoa and order Paramyxida infecting the digestive system of several bivalve species and inducing physiological disorders and eventually death of the animal. Infection with _Marteilia refringens_ covers infection with _M. refringens_ including types M and O. http://www.oie.int/index.php?id=2439&L=0&htmfile=chapitre_marteilia_refringens.htm

Marteiliosis due to _Marteilia refringens_ occurs in Europe where it infects flat oysters, _Ostrea edulis_ and mussels, _Mytilus edulis_ and _M. galloprovincialis_. Type M is more often detected in mussels and type O in flat oysters, however co-infection exists. This last event seems to be restricted to areas where the prevalence of the disease is high. http://www.eurl-mollusc.eu/Scientific-activities/Marteilia-refringens

The causal agent of _Marteilia refringens_ is not a risk to human health. http://www.inspection.gc.ca/animals/aquatic-animals/diseases/reportable/marteilia-refringens/fact-sheet/eng/1362602145346/1362602305193. - Mod.CRD

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4864174,32342.]
